<div class="api-docs">
  <h1>API Documentation</h1>

  <h2>1. Get User by Username</h2>
  <div class="endpoint">
    <strong>Endpoint:</strong>
    <code>GET /api/users/:username</code>
  </div>
  <div class="description">
    Retrieves a user's details by their username.
    <strong>Status Codes:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>200:</strong> Success, returns user data.</li>
      <li><strong>404:</strong> User not found.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <h2>2. Get Leaderboard</h2>
  <div class="endpoint">
    <strong>Endpoint:</strong>
    <code>GET /api/leaderboard</code>
  </div>
  <div class="description">
    Fetches the top 10 users sorted by the number of coins.
    <strong>Status Codes:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>200:</strong> Success, returns leaderboard data.</li>
      <li><strong>404:</strong> No users found.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <h2>3. Get Waiting Rooms</h2>
  <div class="endpoint">
    <strong>Endpoint:</strong>
    <code>GET /api/rooms</code>
  </div>
  <div class="description">
    Lists all available waiting rooms.
    <strong>Status Codes:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>200:</strong> Success, returns waiting room data.</li>
      <li><strong>404:</strong> No rooms found.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
